The paper discusses the use of Deep Convolutional Neural Networks for image retrieval, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The focus is on training the models using the triplet loss function, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of hand-engineered features, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of larger models and more training data, which are common topics in multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
